#k neighbor model for points
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier

testscores = []
trainscores = []

# for loop from 1 through 14 to train model and append data
for i in range(1,15):
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(i)
    knn.fit(x_pts_train,y_pts_train)
    trainscores.append(knn.score(x_pts_train,y_pts_train))
    testscores.append(knn.score(x_pts_test,y_pts_test))

#k-value using elbow method
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
distortions = []
K = range(1,10)
for k in K:
    kmeanModel = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    kmeanModel.fit(nbadf)
    distortions.append(kmeanModel.inertia_)
plt.figure(figsize = (16,8))
plt.plot(K, distortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Distortion')
plt.title('The Elbow Method showing the optimal k')
plt.show()
